==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Black letter
<hw>Black" let`ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>The old English or Gothic
letter, in which the Early English manuscripts were written, and the
first English books were printed. It was conspicuous for its blackness.
See <er>Type</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

